   @('new-name'),
   @('new-enable'),
   @('thm-name'),
   @('thm-enable'),
   @('verify-guards'),
   @('hints'),
   @('print'), and
   @('show-only')
   are the homonymous inputs to @(tsee restrict),
   before being processed.
   These formal parameters have no types because they may be any values."

  "@('call') is the call to @(tsee restrict) supplied by the user."

  "@('old$'),
   @('restriction$'),
   @('undefined$'),
   @('new-name$'),
   @('new-enable$'),
   @('thm-name$'),
   @('thm-enable$'),
   @('verify-guards$'),
